IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: The core values of Luna Dance Institute are to provide access to dance to all children community service with integrity and creativity as the foundation for dance in education. These are the driving forces behind Luna's unique programmatic and organizational structures. Luna's Professional Learning Component and it's Model Programs work in tandem to bring high quality standard-based dance learning to all children while improving dance teaching practice and advancing the field of dance education.
IRS990.MissionDesc: The mission of Luna Kids Dance is to bring creativity equity and community to every child's life through the art of dance.
IRS990.Desc: Luna Kids Dance brings art experiences to more than 30,000 children and 400 artists teachers and social service providers each and every year. Over 31 years Luna has grown from a local dance studio to a nationally recognized dance education providing services to children and the adults who impact their lives. In 2022-23 Luna continued our post-COVID Adaptation work funded by the William & Flora Hewlett Foundation to strengthen our infrastructure and expanded the following program areas: 1 Professional Learning returning our nationally-recognized Summer Institute to in-person participation expanding our workshops and seminars in early childhood education and providing practitioner exchanges consultation and mentoring to over 400 artists and teachers. 2 Building Cultures of Dance in partnership with Oakland Unified School District-ECE and VAPA departments Berkeley Unified School District-ECE San Francisco Ballet and Marin Office of Education-ECE. This partnership work was comprised of professional development workshops model classes taught to students leadership development and mentorship of new dance teachers hired by the districts in response to Proposition 28. We continued offering embodied parent education through our MPACT moving parents and children together program at Project Pride part of Lifelong Medical Care. 3 While our new studios are being renovated we continued offering free family dance classes at local public parks and libraries presented community panels and forums virtually and hosted a free community event open to the general public and live-streamed as a public education opportunity.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Accounting principles generally accepted in the United States of America require management to evaluate tax positions taken by the Organization and recognize a tax liability or asset if the Organization has taken an uncertain position that more likely than not would not be sustained upon examination by the Internal Revenue Service or the Franchise Tax Board. Management has analyzed the tax positions taken by the Organization and has concluded that as of June 30 2023 there are no uncertain tax positions taken or expected to be taken that would require recognition of a liability or asset or disclosure in the financial statements. The Organization is subject to routine audits by taxing jurisdictions; however there are currently no audits for any tax periods in question. Management believes it is no longer subject to tax examinations for years prior to June 30 2019.

Prior to filing the tax return it is reviewed by management a member of the Board of Directors and the executive director. After full review with modifications if necessary the full voting Board of Directors approves the reviewed documents. Once approved the form is signed and filed.

On a yearly basis board members are asked to confirm that they have followed established policies and that there were no conflicts during the fiscal year. In addition the conflict-of-interest policies are addressed at each quarterly meeting and board members are asked to abstain from voting if they lack information or have any potential ethical conflicts.

In accordance with IRS Rules and Regulations the members of the Board of Directors periodically review the compensation of all high-level personnel. Efforts are made to secure compensation data from industry sources in order to determine competitiveness and appropriateness of salaries. Effort is made to ensure that the process is thorough and transparent in accordance with IRS guidelines and the Organization's policies and procedures.

All of the Organization's governing documents financial statements and legal filings are maintained in a secure environment and are available for inspection. Form 990 is posted annually to Guidestar.com where it is available for viewing as an electronic copy and is also available in hard copy form at the Organization's office in Berkeley CA.

The review report financial statements are reviewed by management a member of the Board of Directors and the executive director. After full review with modifications if necessary the full voting Board of Directors approves the review report financial statements.
